Project Layout

Set up the layout of our tutorial site, including the routing for it using React Router.
We'll use a library called reactstrap for easy use of Bootstrap components in our project.
We'll set up our initial components for structuring the app.
We'll set up a small amount of styling for each of the components.

react-router-dom
For our routing for this app, we'll add react-router-dom. To install this, run the following
npm install react-router-dom --save

You'll be setting up React Router momentarily, but in the mean time, you can read more about React Router here. 
reactstrap
Again, React itself is a library, a single file that we use to make React components. There are hundreds of other libraries and tools that we can use in conjunction with a React application. reactstrap is a handy library for adding Bootstrap to our application. Let's get it started.
install bootstrap
Install bootstrap 
npm install bootstrap --save

Import bootstrap.css in App.js. Make sure it's above the App.css import.
    import React, { Component } from 'react';
